article.headline: CS Bakersfield 57, Cal Poly-SLO 52
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Senior guard Terrence Johns came off the bench to score 18 points as Cal State Bakersfield beat Cal Poly 57-52 Wednesday. Cal Poly rallied from seven down in the final minutes to pull within 51-50 with 1:31 left, but Donovan Bragg hit a jumper and two free throws down the stretch. Cal State Bakersfield (8-20) held the Mustangs to 1-for-14 from 3-point range and 42 percent shooting from the floor. Chaz Thomas scored 13 points for Cal Poly (7-18), which finished the first half on a 7-0 run and led 34-28 at halftime.
